# ECUBE — Frontend Addendum

Apply when touching Vue, frontend components, templates, CSS, frontend tests, or browser interactions.

## Trust Boundary

- The frontend is untrusted
- The frontend is a Vue 3 SPA served by FastAPI
- The frontend communicates only through the HTTPS API
- The frontend must never touch hardware or the database directly

## Accessibility

- All interactive elements must be keyboard operable
- Prefer native elements such as `button`, `a`, and `input`
- Focus order must be logical
- ARIA must be correct
- Inputs must have labels
- Modals must trap focus
- Icons must have accessible labels

## Directory Browser and Tree View

- Rows must be keyboard accessible
- Do not rely on `<tr @click>` without keyboard handlers
- Support arrow-key navigation
- Screen readers must distinguish files from directories

## CSS and Templates

- Remove unused styles
- Keep class names aligned with template usage

## Frontend Validation

- Test keyboard interaction and accessibility-sensitive behavior for changed components
- Preserve API-only trust boundaries in UI flows